<p><b>Shirin Ebadi</b> (<a href="/wiki/Persian_language" title="Persian language">Persian</a>: <span lang="fa" xml:lang="fa">شیرین عبادی</span> - <i>Širin Ebâdi</i>; born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1947-06-21"><a href="/wiki/June_21" title="June 21">21 June</a> <a href="/wiki/1947" title="1947">1947</a></span>) is an <a href="/wiki/Iran" title="Iran">Iranian</a> <a href="/wiki/Lawyer" title="Lawyer">lawyer</a>, <a href="/wiki/Human_rights" title="Human rights">human rights</a> activist and founder of Children's Rights Support Association in Iran. On <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2003-10-10"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="10-10"><a href="/wiki/October_10" title="October 10">October 10</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2003" title="2003">2003</a></span>, Ebadi was awarded the <a href="/wiki/Nobel_Peace_Prize" title="Nobel Peace Prize">Nobel Peace Prize</a> for her significant and pioneering efforts for democracy and human rights, especially women's, children's, and refugee rights. She was the first ever Iranian to have received the prize.</p>
